Description:
Oversized 1 Bedroom Beauty
Positioned at the rear of the block away from Hoddle Street, is this spacious one bedroom apartment offering all the modern convenience and lifestyle that Collingwood has to offer.
Featuring a modern kitchen, a bright living/dining room, a spacious bedroom including large built-in robes and an immaculate central bathroom. Additional features include reverse cycle heating/cooling system in both the bedroom and living, secure car space on title, common courtyard, and secure intercom entry.
Victoria Parade trams within a stone’s throw, it's also walking distance to vibrant shopping strips, renowned restaurants, East Melbourne hospital precinct, Fitzroy Gardens and the CBD.
Insights: 234/3 Hoddle Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
The lifestyle you imagined
In a quiet residential street, you can make the most of cool, contemporary, city-edge living moments to cafes, restaurants, bars and transport with this two bedroom plus open study apartment. Seconds to Smith Street in a boutique block of 19, it's freshly painted and welcomes in uplifting natural light and boasts a living/meals/kitchen starring expansive stone countertops, electric cooking facilities and a dishwasher, in stainless steel. A sliding glass door leads to an inviting northerly balcony with retractable awning, fashionably presented double bedrooms come with built-in robes and there's a bathroom on each of the two floors. Completed by a concealed laundry, heating/cooling in bedrooms and living areas, secure entrance with video intercom, storage cage and OSP it's easily maintained.

Description:
Stanley Street Space & Sunshine
Located just steps from bustling Smith Street, but overlooking a quiet cul-de-sac, is this spacious two bedroom apartment in the sought-after 10 Stanley Street complex.
A generous open plan living and dining space with polished floorboards opens onto a large north-facing private balcony with unobstructed views, a rarity in this popular suburb.
Modern and well-appointed, the light-filled home also features a stylish kitchen with quality stainless steel appliances and a sleek central bathroom.
Additional features include double reverse cycle heating/cooling, a secure undercover car space (non-stacker) and large storage cage on title and secure video intercom entry through a marble-lined foyer.
With an unbeatable location just minutes from supermarkets, trams, cafes and everything Collingwood has to offer, this apartment is ideal for either an owner-occupier or an astute investor. An inspection is certain to impress.
Insights: 4/10 Stanley Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

AUCTION - UNLESS SOLD PRIOR

Description:
The Oxley penthouse. Outstanding city to ranges views
Sensational city skyline views both uninterrupted and protected bring a spectacular edge to the light-filled spaces of this stunning Oxley penthouse apartment. Award-winning Elenberg Fraser architect's sublime lifestyle complex is the only one in Collingwood with a communal pool accompanied with a BBQ terrace. On the top-floor with secure lift access plus fixed on-title basement car space right next to the lift and 2 basement storage cages, this 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment offered for the first time presents an exclusive opportunity in the vibrant Foy & Gibson precinct. Includes brilliant living and dining room with full-height double-glazed doors to entertainment terrace, premium Miele stone kitchen, laundry, mirror BIRs, gallery hanging system, heating/cooling and timber floors. A rare penthouse lifestyle experience near Smith Street.

Description:
Derby House, circa 1872. Period elegance & modern style.
Behind this two-storey Regency facade is a stunning architect designed home, showcasing a lesson in simplicity and elegance offering light filled, generous living spaces and a north facing private garden with OSP from Langridge Street. This period terrace, adjacent to Oxford Street Park, is offering a prime lifestyle location on the East Melbourne border, minutes from the CBD, with the Gertrude Street design & arts precinct and vibrant Smith Street on its doorstep. The home features a separate living room, spacious and inviting living/dining opening to a well-equipped kitchen, stylish central bathroom, walk-in cellar/storage and garden area. Upstairs the large master bedroom includes a chic ensuite with freestanding bath and built in robes, followed by the second double bedroom with built in robes, all with views overlooking the park. Includes hydronic heating, double glazing, polished timber floors, plantation shutters, a-c and alarm. Mixed-Use Zoning and three street frontages providing a range of uses for this versatile property which was originally a corner store, an office building and now a private and stunning home. Please note this property is eligible for 2 parking permits.
Insights: 22 Derby Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Spacious, Flexible, Indoor/Outdoor Entertainer
Unexpectedly spacious and enviably private, this 3-storey, 4-bedroom, 3 terrace & courtyard townhouse presents rare executive and family-friendly excellence in a fabulous location for inner city living. Refreshed with modern verve; it's ready to move straight in, spread out and entertain family and friends in high style, indoors and out.
Ground level: Lock up garage (internal access), and security entry to front courtyard, laundry, powder room and open-plan kitchen, dining and living with black-granite benchtops, stainless-steel appliances and mosaic-tile splashbacks.
First floor: Tiled bathroom with bath/shower and three bright bedrooms with built-in wardrobes (or 2 plus extra living); 2 adjoining sunny, scenic terraces.
Second and top floor: Majestic master bedroom with fitted walk-in wardrobe, en suite and romantic terrace addressing city lights.
Stroll to trams, shops, cafes, corner pubs, Smith and Brunswick Street action and the city.
High and sloping ceilings, hardwood floors, soft carpet, storage and R/C heating/cooling complement a sophisticated, low-maintenance package and smart investment opportunity.

Description:
City living at its best
Be part of history with this large 1st floor 1 Bedroom apartment located in part of the prominent former grain silos landmark in Collingwood. The apartment comprises of a large open plan living area with study nook that flows to an entertainer’s balcony. Large bedroom with built in robes, modern bathroom with Euro laundry and extra storage space. With an internal size of over 60 sqm this apartment is a must inspect for those who are looking for space and substance.
Stylish gourmet kitchen, featuring stone benches, S/S appliances, including dishwasher, glass splashback and solid cabinetry. Extras include quality solid timber floors, storage cage, car space, heating/cooling, large outdoor undercover entertainment decking, BBQ and gym facilities, intercom and secure entrance.
The Islington Silos make a defining contribution to the emergence of Collingwood as a highly coveted residential locale and is surrounded by a number of high quality restaurants, bars and cafes; including, Jimmy Grant's, The Gem Bar, Naked For Satan, Stomping Ground Brewery Beer Hall. A short walk to Abbotsford Convent, the Yarra Trail, local galleries, Collingwood Leisure Centre and with easy access by tram to the CBD, and the Eastern and Monash freeways.

Description:
Prized inner-city potential in a north garden setting
A deep north-facing rear garden adds an exceptional alfresco edge to the lifestyle allure of this unique period residence at the open east-end of an historic terrace row. Located in a prime pocket between Smith Street and train station, execute the definitive renovation/extension then enjoy the rewards of indoor-outdoor excellence beyond a captivating façade. Comfortably presented with outstanding potential, this inviting home with early-Victorian origins includes 2 spacious bedrooms, living/dining room with gas space heater and ceiling fan, bright kitchen, bathroom, laundry, reverse-cycle air-conditioning, polished Baltic pine floors, timber decking and established garden. Stroll to cafes, restaurants, nightlife, trams, Victoria Park and Yarra trails. A rare opening with sought-after scope!

Description:
Modern Style, Enviable Lifestyle And City Skyline Views
Boasting high-quality fixtures and fittings throughout, a subdued neutrally-toned interior and spectacular views of the CBD skyline, this exceptional near-new apartment comprises a large open plan living/dining room with well-appointed kitchen (stone bench tops, Miele cookware, integrated Fisher & Paykel dishwasher, soft-closing drawers) that flows onto the wrap-around balcony with uninterrupted city skyline aspect, 2 generously proportioned bedrooms with BIRs (one with balcony access, the other with study space), gleaming central bathroom with floor-to-ceiling tiles and wall-hung toilet, Euro laundry, storage closet and direct access to an expansive common terrace, ideal for entertaining. Perched high above the bustle of vibrant Smith Street shops, cafes and trams, the apartment enjoys an enviable inner-city lifestyle surrounded by popular side-street cafes and gastro pubs, Fitzroy Aquatic Centre and Edinburgh Gardens. Features include timber floors throughout, heating/cooling and secure intercom entry with lift access to basement OSP and storage cage.
